  "prompt": "Why did Pepper Potts leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War? Why wasn\u2019t she in the film?",
  "response": "In \"Captain America: Civil War,\" Pepper Potts, played by Gwyneth Paltrow, is not physically present, and her absence is explained as part of the storyline. The film suggests that Tony Stark (Iron Man) and Pepper are taking a break from their relationship. This separation is mainly attributed to the stress and complications that Tony's life as Iron Man has on their relationship. Tony mentions during a conversation that they are on a break because she needed space, which he interprets as resulting from his inability to step away from his responsibilities as a superhero.\n\nFrom a production standpoint, Gwyneth Paltrow's absence from the film was due to contractual and scheduling reasons. These off-screen factors led to the character\u2019s absence being woven into the plot in a way that affected Tony Stark's emotional state and motivations throughout the film.",
